        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:56PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Shaw, or 20 miles north of Cascade, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort  Shaw, Fort Shaw, Vaughn, and Sun River.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
